The '''Centre for Applied Philosophy, Politics and Ethics''' ('''CAPPE''') is a research center at the [[University of Brighton]]. The Centre is under the directorship of [[Bob Brecher]] and [[Mark Devenney]]. It "researches the links between [[philosophy]], [[critical theory]], [[global ethics]], other disciplines and the wider public."<ref>{{cite web |title=International Consortium of Critical Theory Programs {{!}} Directory of Programs, Centers, and Projects {{!}} Centre for Applied Philosophy, Politics and Ethics |url=http://directory.criticaltheoryconsortium.org/centers/centre-for-applied-philosophy-politics-and-ethics/ |accessdate=28 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Mark Devenney |url=https://theconversation.com/profiles/mark-devenney-332725 |website=The Conversation |accessdate=28 November 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Claes |first1=Tom |title=Cevi - Global Ethics |url=http://www.cevi-globalethics.ugent.be/cappe |website=www.cevi-globalethics.ugent.be}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Centre for Applied Philosophy, Politics and Ethics |url=http://redfilosofia.es/blog/2017/11/22/centre-for-applied-philosophy-politics-and-ethics/ |website=Red española de Filosofía |accessdate=28 November 2018 |language=es-ES |date=22 November 2017}}</ref>
