'''Myology''' is the study of the '''muscular system''', including the study of the structure, function and [[Disease|diseases]] of [[muscle]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Scali-Sheahan|first1=Maura|title=Milady's Standard Professional Barbering|date=2010|publisher=Cengage Learning|location=Clifton Park, N.Y.|isbn=978-1435497153|page=147|edition=5th}}</ref> The muscular system consists of [[skeletal muscle]], which contracts to move or position parts of the body (e.g., the bones that articulate at joints), [[smooth muscle tissue|smooth]] and [[cardiac muscle]] that propels, expels or controls the flow of fluids and contained substance.
